3. AWR-MARS: AUTONOMOUS WALKING ROVER (INDUSTRIAL)

3.1 Core Mission

Primary manufacturer of capital goods: steel production, tool fabrication, machine components, and rover reproduction.

3.2 Specifications

```
Class:              Heavy Industrial Quadruped
Height:             2.8 m (operational, adjustable ±0.5 m)
Mass:               850 kg (dry)
Payload:            400 kg continuous, 600 kg peak
Power System:       120 kWh Li-S solid-state battery
Locomotion:         4 legs × 6 DOF each
Construction:       Ti-6Al-4V frame, CFRP panels
Design Life:        10 Earth years (5 Mars years)
```

3.3 Tool Ecosystem (QSI-1 Standard)

```
Tool Head           Mass    Power    Function
RH-2 Harvester      85 kg   8 kW     Regolith mining with ore grading
GR-4 Gripper        45 kg   2 kW     4-finger manipulation (500N grip)
LA-3 Laser          65 kg   12 kW    Additive manufacturing (2kW fiber)
IC-1 Crucible       120 kg  15 kW    Mobile smelting (5kg batches)
LW-X Welder         55 kg   10 kW    Structural welding (3kW laser)
MS-1 Scanner        25 kg   0.5 kW   Site survey (LIDAR + GPR + spectrometer)
```

3.4 Production Capabilities

```
Steel Production Chain:
1. Extraction:    RH-2 mines hematite-rich regolith @ 250 kg/hour
2. Beneficiation: Magnetic separation → 35% Fe concentrate
3. Smelting:      Carbothermic reduction @ 1,500°C → 95% pure iron
4. Refining:      Basic oxygen process → steel alloys

Output Metrics:
- Per Sol:        120 kg iron → 100 kg steel
- Per Mars Year:  21,600 kg steel
- Energy:         15 kWh per 100 kg steel
```

3.5 Self-Replication Pathway

```
Year 1: Fabricate spare parts and tool heads
Year 2: Manufacture structural components for AWR-05
Year 3: Assemble first Mars-built rover (70% local mass)
Year 5: Complete rover reproduction (90% local mass)
```

---

4. ASR-MARS: AUTONOMOUS SUPPORT ROVER (LOGISTICS)

4.1 Core Mission

Bulk material handling: excavation, processing, and continuous supply to construction sites.

4.2 Specifications

```
Class:              Heavy Logistics Rover
Locomotion:         6-wheel rocker-bogie (optimized for payload)
Mass:               1,500 kg
Payload:            800 kg internal hopper + 1,200 kg towed trailer
Power:              400V DC from RTG/solar hybrid
Mining Depth:       2.0 m (below perchlorate layer)
Processing Rate:    500 kg/hour continuous
```

4.3 Material Processing System

```
Excavation (RS-D1):
├── Continuous bucket-drum excavator
├── 0.38g-optimized digging kinematics
├── Bypasses surface dust (0-30cm)
└── Target: stable silicate layer (30-200cm)

Processing (RS-P1):
├── Vibratory sieve (3-stage separation)
├── Magnetic separator (Fe-rich fines)
├── Centrifugal concentrator (sulfates)
└── Output streams:
    ├── Structural aggregate (coarse, 40%)
    ├── Sintering fines (fine dust, 30%)
    └── Sulfate concentrate (binder, 20%)
    └── Waste tailings (10%)

Thermal Management (RS-T1):
├── 130°C heated hopper (sulfur storage)
├── Waste heat utilization from RTG
├── Solar-thermal backup (2m² concentrator)
└── Pneumatic transfer to ARC-Mars @ 50 kg/min
```

4.4 Logistics Protocols

```
The Continuous Feed Protocol:
1. ASR scouts deposit within 500m of construction site
2. Excavates and processes 800 kg batch (1.6 hours)
3. Returns to ARC-Mars construction site
4. Docks via QSI-1 umbilical (pressurized transfer)
5. Pneumatic transfer during ARC printing operation
6. Cycle time: 3 hours (including travel)
```

---

5. ARC-MARS: AUTONOMOUS REGOLITH CONSTRUCTION ROVER (ARCHITECTURE)

5.1 Core Mission

Transformation of processed materials into permanent, radiation-shielded habitats.

5.2 Specifications

```
Class:              Heavy Construction Quadruped  
Height:             3.2 m (telescopic mast extended)
Mass:               1,200 kg
Printing Payload:   800 kg (material reservoir)
Construction Reach: 8.0 m radial from center
Accuracy:           ±1 mm deposition control
Power:              400V DC, 20 hours/sol operation
```

5.3 Construction Toolkit (QSI-C Standard)

```
Tool Head           Function
RC-E1              Regolith concrete extrusion (sulfur-based)
RC-M1              Microwave sintering (10-20 kW)
RC-L1              Laser precision sintering/vitrification
RC-B1              Brick/block placement (hexagonal geometry)
RC-C1              Compaction & leveling
RC-S1              Structural scanner (ultrasound + thermal)
```

5.4 ARC-8 Habitat Unit Specifications

```
Geometry:
├── Diameter:           8.0 m
├── Internal Height:    4.5 m (center), 2.8 m (edges)
├── Floor Area:         ≈50 m²
├── Volume:             ≈268 m³
└── Crew Capacity:      6 humans (optimal), 8 (emergency)

7-Layer Wall Structure (inside → out):
1. Atmosphere:          101.3 kPa Earth-standard mix
2. Liner:               Kevlar/polymer membrane (Earth-supplied)
3. Reinforcement:       Steel tensioning hoops (AWR-fabricated)
4. Core Structure:      Sulfur-regolith concrete (40-50 MPa)
5. Thermal Gap:         5 cm loose regolith insulation (R-value ≈ 20)
6. Radiation Shield:    2.5 m sintered regolith (500 g/cm²)
7. Exterior Glaze:      Vitrified glass layer (laser-formed)

Structural Performance:
├── Radiation Attenuation:  99.9% (≈0.001 mSv/day inside)
├── Thermal Stability:      ΔT < 5°C diurnal at 1m depth
├── Micrometeorite:         Survives 1 cm @ 10 km/s
├── Pressure Safety:        2.0 safety factor (200 kPa burst)
└── Seismic:               Withstands 0.5g horizontal acceleration
```

5.5 27-Sol Construction Sequence

```
Phase I: Site Preparation (Sol 1-3)
├── Sol 1: ASR-Mars clears and levels 15m diameter site
├── Sol 2: ARC-Mars microwave-sinters foundation pad
└── Sol 3: AWR-Mars installs foundation anchors & utility conduits

Phase II: Wall Construction (Sol 4-18)
├── Sol 4-5: AWR places steel door frame and airlock foundation
├── Sol 6-18: ARC continuous extrusion of sulfur-concrete walls
   ├── Print rate: 0.5 m/hour vertical
   ├── ASR continuous feed (3-hour cycles)
   └── AWR installs vertical steel tendons every 90°

Phase III: Dome Completion (Sol 19-24)
├── Sol 19-21: ARC prints geodesic dome using RC-B1 block placement
├── Sol 22-24: ASR berms 2.5m radiation shield around exterior
└── Concurrent: AWR installs internal utility spine

Phase IV: Finishing & Validation (Sol 25-27)
├── Sol 25: ARC vitrifies exterior with RC-L1 laser
├── Sol 26: AWR inflates and seals internal liner
├── Sol 27: Structural health monitoring (vibrational analysis)
└── Handover: AIADN marks unit "Habitable" in settlement map
```

