6. INTEGRATED OPERATIONS: CONSTRUCTION SWARM PROTOCOL

6.1 Normal Operations Coordination

```
AIADN Construction Orchestration:
├── Task Allocation:   Dynamic assignment based on rover capability & proximity
├── Resource Flow:     ASR → ARC material transfer synchronized with print head position
├── Conflict Avoidance: 3D path planning with 5m separation minimum
├── Progress Tracking:  Digital twin updates every 15 minutes
└── Quality Assurance:  Continuous scanner validation during construction
```

6.2 Emergency Protocols

6.2.1 Solar Particle Event Response (GLE Protocol)

```
Detection (Radiation > 100 mSv/hr):
├── T+0: All rovers receive AIADN "Storm Warning"
├── T+1 min: ARC-Mars executes "Hard Cap" - laser vitrifies current layer
├── T+2 min: ASR-Mars positions as windward/radiation shield
├── T+5 min: All rovers enter "Hibernation Lock" - joints locked, minimum systems
└── Duration: Maintain until radiation < 10 mSv/hr for 1 hour

Recovery:
├── Post-storm structural scan (thermal delta analysis)
├── Re-heat and bond interface if cooling gradient > 50°C/cm
├── Resume printing from vitrified interface
└── Estimated delay: 12-48 hours depending on storm severity
```

6.2.2 Rover Failure Response (MEDEVAC Protocol)

```
Failure Classification:
├── Level 1 (Minor): Continue with compensation (e.g., 3-leg gait)
├── Level 2 (Major): Buddy-system repair at site
├── Level 3 (Critical): Return to base for workshop repair
└── Level 4 (Catastrophic): Parts donor for other units

Buddy-System Repair:
├── Nearest capable rover responds within 30 minutes
├── Standardized repair procedures for 32 common failures
├── Tool swap via QSI-1 interface
├── Typical repair time: 2-8 hours depending on failure
└── AIADN automatically reschedules construction timeline
```

6.3 Dust Storm Operations

```
Protocol: DUST-SHROUD (Dust Storm Heuristic Response for Operations Under Degradation)
Phase 1 (Visibility < 1 km):
├── Rovers complete current task segment
├── Return to base or sheltered location
├── Deploy electrostatic dust shedding

Phase 2 (Visibility < 100 m):
├── Anchor to ground or structure
├── Positive pressure purge of sensitive components
├── Enter low-power mode
├── Estimated downtime: 2-5 sols

Phase 3 (Recovery):
├── Self-cleaning cycle (vibration + electrostatic)
├── Sensor calibration
├── System check before resuming operations
```

