7. SETTLEMENT SCALING STRATEGY

7.1 Growth Phases

Phase 1: Bootstrap (Year 1-2)

```
Goal:        Prove industrial and construction capability
Infrastructure:
├── 4 AWR-Mars, 2 ARC-Mars, 2 ASR-Mars operational
├── Foundry Core producing 100 kg steel/sol
├── Power: 40 kW Kilopower + 20 kW solar
└── Output: 4 ARC-8 habitats (crew capacity: 24)

Key Milestones:
├── Sol 15: First steel produced
├── Sol 30: First habitat structural shell complete
├── Sol 90: First interconnected habitat cluster
└── Year 2: Rover reproduction begins (AWR-05 fabrication)
```

Phase 2: Expansion (Year 3-5)

```
Goal:        Scale to 50-person settlement with specialized districts
Infrastructure:
├── Rover fleet: 8 AWR, 4 ARC, 4 ASR
├── Steel production: 300 kg/sol
├── Power: 200 kW (fission augmented)
├── Habitats: 12 ARC-8 units + specialized structures
└── Population capacity: 75 humans

District Formation:
├── Residential Cluster (6 habitats)
├── Research District (3 habitats + lab facilities)
├── Industrial Zone (foundry, machine shops, storage)
├── Agricultural Experimentation (1 habitat + greenhouse)
└── Common Areas (2 habitats for dining, recreation)
```

Phase 3: Self-Sufficiency (Year 6-10)

```
Goal:        Closed-loop material economy, city-scale infrastructure
Infrastructure:
├── Rover fleet: 20+ units (specialized variants)
├── Manufacturing: Complete rover reproduction from local materials
├── Power: 1 MW+ (fission reactor + large solar array)
├── Habitats: 50+ units, including subterranean expansion
└── Population capacity: 300+ humans

Urban Development:
├── Hexagonal city layout (1 km diameter)
├── Pressurized transit tunnels between districts
├── Subsurface expansion (10-20m depth for radiation-free spaces)
├── Redundant life support systems (3× required capacity)
└── Export economy begins (data, unique research, eventually manufactured goods)
```

7.2 City Planning: The Hexagonal Hub Architecture

```
Settlement Layout:
├── Central Nexus:      Life support, power distribution, AIADN core
├── Primary Arteries:   6 main tunnels radiating at 60° intervals
├── District Cells:     Hexagonal clusters of 7 habitats each
├── Industrial Ring:    Perimeter zone for noisy/dirty operations
└── Green Belt:        Future expansion zone with radiation berms

Advantages:
├── Minimizes transit distance (average 0.5× radius)
├── Structural stability under internal pressure
├── Efficient utility distribution
├── Natural expansion pathways
└── Multiple egress routes for safety
```

7.3 Subsurface Development Strategy

```
Depth           Purpose                           Construction Method
0-5m            Surface habitats                  ARC-Mars standard construction
5-10m           Critical infrastructure           ARC-Mars with excavation support
10-20m          Radiation-free living spaces      Mining equipment + ARC adaptation
20-50m          Storage, backup systems           Natural lava tube utilization
50m+            Future expansion                  TBD based on geological findings
```

