8. HUMAN INTEGRATION & INTERFACE

8.1 Pre-Arrival Infrastructure

```
Crew Arrival Thresholds:
├── Minimum:     4 habitable ARC-8 units (crew of 6 each → 24 capacity)
├── Comfortable: 8 units + interconnected tunnels (48 capacity)
├── Recommended: 12 units + specialized facilities (72 capacity)
└── Safety Buffer: 30% excess capacity at arrival

Crew Tasks on Arrival (First 90 Sols):
├── System Verification: Physical inspection of AIADN-built infrastructure
├── Science Initiation: Begin research programs in ready laboratories
├── Expansion Oversight: Direct rover fleet for priority construction
├── Agriculture Start: Establish greenhouse operations
└── Maintenance: Human-led repair of complex systems
```

8.2 Human-Robot Interface Evolution

```
Phase 1 (Pre-arrival): Full AIADN autonomy with Earth oversight
Phase 2 (Crew arrival): Mixed autonomy - humans set priorities, AI executes
Phase 3 (Settlement): Humans manage high-level strategy, AI handles operations
Phase 4 (City): AIADN as municipal utility, human creative direction

Control Hierarchy:
├── Level 5: Full autonomy (AI decides objectives based on high-level goals)
├── Level 4: Supervised autonomy (AI proposes, human approves)
├── Level 3: Task autonomy (human specifies task, AI determines execution)
├── Level 2: Shared control (human and AI operate together)
└── Level 1: Manual control (human direct operation, rare emergency use)
```

8.3 Crew Time Allocation Projection

```
Early Settlement (Year 1-2):
├── 40%: Science & research
├── 30%: Settlement expansion oversight
├── 20%: System maintenance & repair
└── 10%: Personal & administrative

Mature Settlement (Year 5+):
├── 50%: Specialized research/creative pursuits
├── 20%: Settlement governance & planning
├── 20%: Education & training
└── 10%: Maintenance (mostly supervisory)
```

