9. RISK MITIGATION FRAMEWORK

9.1 Technical Risk Matrix

```
Risk                            Probability   Impact   Mitigation Strategy
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Dust ingress into mechanisms    High          Medium   Triple sealing + positive pressure
Sulfur concrete thermal creep   Medium        High     Steel tendon pre-tensioning + thermal mass
Actuator failure (walking)      Medium        High     Buddy-system repair + 3-leg gait capability
Solar storm during construction Low           Critical GLE Protocol + hardened electronics
AIADN coordination failure      Low           High     Distributed control + human override
Resource depletion (local)      Medium        Medium   ASR prospecting + material recycling
```

9.2 Contingency Scenarios

9.2.1 Multiple Rover Failure

```
Response: LAZARUS Protocol
1. Functional rovers assess remaining capability
2. AIADN recalculates construction timeline with reduced fleet
3. Prioritize habitat completion over expansion
4. Functional rovers begin fabrication of replacement components
5. If <50% fleet operational, request Earth resupply
Recovery time: 90-180 sols to full capability
```

9.2.2 Foundry Core Failure

```
Response: PHOENIX Protocol
1. Activate mobile smelting (IC-1 tool on AWR-Mars)
2. Reduce steel production to essential items only
3. Prioritize repair parts for Foundry Core
4. AWR-Mars fabricates replacement components
5. Reactivate within 30 sols (estimated)
```

9.2.3 Complete Communication Loss with Earth

```
Response: HERMIT Protocol
1. AIADN assumes full autonomous control
2. Continue according to last approved construction plan
3. Store all data locally for eventual transmission
4. Periodic beacon signals indicate status
5. Estimated autonomous operation duration: 2+ years
```

9.3 Redundancy Architecture

```
Critical Systems             Redundancy Level   Backup Activation
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Power                        Triple (Kilopower, solar, batteries)  Automatic
Communication                Dual mesh + beacon  Automatic
Compute                     Triple modular      Voting system
Structural integrity        Buddy-system repair  AIADN dispatch
Life support (completed habitat)  Dual systems   Manual or automatic
```

