```
Phase A: Component Development (Year 0-1)
├── TRL 3→4: Lab validation of critical components
├── Focus: QSI-1 interface, sulfur concrete, walking kinematics
└── Deliverable: Component test reports

Phase B: System Integration (Year 1-2)
├── TRL 4→5: Integrated rover prototypes (AWR-E1, ARC-E1, ASR-E1)
├── Mars-yard testing (1:1 scale, simulated gravity)
└── Deliverable: Functional prototypes

Phase C: Field Testing (Year 2-3)
├── TRL 5→6: Mars-analog field campaigns
├── Locations: Atacama, Devon Island, Mauna Ulu
├── 1,000+ hours of autonomous operation
└── Deliverable: Field readiness certification
```

10.2 Flight Qualification & Deployment (Years 3-6)

```
Phase D: Flight Unit Development (Year 3-4)
├── TRL 6→7: Space-qualified design
├── Vibration, thermal vacuum, radiation testing
├── Deliverable: Flight-certified units

Phase E: First Mission Launch (Year 5)
├── Vulcan-1: 25,000 kg to Mars surface
├── Landing site: Pre-characterized with orbital assets
├── Initial operations: 30 sols autonomous checkout
└── Success criteria: First steel produced by Sol 15

Phase F: Scaling Deployment (Year 6+)
├── Additional triad units every 26-month launch window
├── Human precursor missions (Year 7-8)
├── First crew arrival (Year 8-9, dependent on infrastructure)
└── Continuous expansion thereafter
```

