APPENDICES

Appendix A: Acronyms & Definitions

```
AWR: Autonomous Walking Rover (Industrial)
ARC: Autonomous Regolith Construction Rover (Architecture)
ASR: Autonomous Support Rover (Logistics)
MSAT: Martian Settlement Autonomy Triad
AIADN: Artificial Intelligence Autonomous Deployed Network
QSI: Quick-Swap Interface (QSI-1: Standard, QSI-C: Construction)
TRL: Technology Readiness Level
GLE: Ground Level Enhancement (solar particle event)
RTG: Radioisotope Thermoelectric Generator
CFRP: Carbon Fiber Reinforced Polymer
DOF: Degrees of Freedom
```

Appendix B: Material Properties Reference

```
Martian Regolith (processed):
├── Bulk density: 1.6-2.0 g/cm³ (compacted)
├── Thermal conductivity: 0.02-0.08 W/m·K (loose)
└── Specific heat: 800-1,000 J/kg·K

Sulfur-Regolith Concrete:
├── Compressive strength: 40-50 MPa
├── Thermal expansion: 15-25 × 10⁻⁶ /°C
├── Melt temperature: 115-140°C
└── Radiation resistance: Excellent (high hydrogen content)

Martian Steel (AWR-produced):
├── Yield strength: 350-400 MPa
├── Composition: Fe-C-Ni-Cr (local additives)
└── Radiation embrittlement: Moderate (requires shielding)

Vitrified Regolith (laser sintered):
├── Compressive strength: 100-200 MPa
├── Thermal shock resistance: Moderate
└── Radiation shielding: Excellent (high density)
```

