EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

This white paper presents the complete mathematical and engineering foundations for the Martian Settlement Autonomy Triad (MSAT)—three specialized robotic systems (AWR, ARC, ASR) that autonomously transform raw Martian regolith into habitable infrastructure. We provide closed-form solutions for mobility, material science, thermal management, and autonomous coordination, enabling the bootstrap of permanent human settlement with 92% local material utilization.

Key Innovations

1. Closed-form mobility equations for quadrupedal walking in 0.38g with dust interaction
2. Sulfur-regolith concrete thermodynamics with Mars-specific creep and radiation models
3. AIADN distributed control with provable stability guarantees
4. QSI-1 interface standardization enabling tool ecosystem emergence
5. Mass-leverage economic model with exponential return on investment

