9. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP

9.1 Technology Development Timeline

Phase 1: Earth Validation (Years 1-3)

1. QSI-1 Interface: Test to 10,000 cycles with Mars dust simulant
2. Sulfur Concrete: Validate strength, creep, radiation resistance
3. Walking Dynamics: 1:1 prototypes in simulated 0.38g (counterweights)

Phase 2: Integrated Testing (Years 4-6)

1. Mars Yard: 1-acre simulated terrain with dust, slopes, obstacles
2. End-to-end: ASR mines → AWR processes → ARC builds (small scale)
3. Autonomy: 1,000 hours unsupervised operation

Phase 3: Mars Deployment (Years 7-10)

1. Vulcan-1: First triad to Mars
2. Expansion: Additional triads every launch window
3. Human arrival: When 12+ habitats complete

9.2 Critical Path Analysis

Longest path: Sulfur concrete validation → Habitat structural testing → Human rating.
Estimated: 8 years to first crew.

